### Still relying on real estate to promote economic growth? China must re -consider

* Stephen Mcdonell * BBC reporter in China

8:18 am on July 7, 2023![] [](Images/BBC Chinese/2023-07-07T08-18-28.000Z/_130310367_2a414963-ef67-479c-9f6d-73f5fec431a7.jpg)Image source, Joyce LiU/BBC

Image adding text,

Zibo's outdoor barbecue provides people with delicious and low -cost leisure diet.

**** Zibo, Shandong Province, is experiencing a wave of outdoor barbecue. ** **

People from all over China come here to taste the famous lamb skewers, which has become a legend in social media.

This is a very noisy experience, and it is definitely not suitable for timid people.

The streets are crowded with people. You sit on a small plastic chair, drink beer, roll the meat pieces with the local onion cakes, and all sides are karaoke.

At first glance, these people seem to show a strong rebound after the emergency state of the crown epidemic -but according to economists, the truth is not the case.

They said that this is more that people have found a cheap and delicious choice under the face of great pressure on household income.

![](Images/BBC Chinese/2023-07-07T08-18-28.000Z/_130310874_bbqzibo3.jpg)Image source, Joyce LiU/BBC

Image adding text,

The lamb skewers and karaoke of Zibo barbecue restaurants have attracted people from all over the country.

A shirtless man told us that this was the ideal place for him and his family on the hot summer night, and the cost performance of this gameplay was in line with the current reality.

"This place is very suitable for the people," he said. "It is difficult to make money recently, but it is still easy to spend money. After three years of epidemic, the economy is just recovering slowly."

Chinese university graduates are particularly seriously impacted by economic downturn, and the unemployment rate has been hovering at 20%or more.

Some students are disturbed by their future.

"Yes, I'm worried," said a girl who was about to graduate. "The competition is fierce and it is difficult to find a job. All my classmates have the same pressure."

For those who have a job, economic protection is an important reason for their unwillingness to spend more money.

They are worried that they may accidentally fall into the ranks of unemployment, and in many cases, the biggest investment of their family is not as valuable as they originally imagined.

China's real estate industry is under tremendous pressure.

[Video-1-Link:/WS/AV-EMBEDS/CPS/ZHONGWEN/SIMP/Chinese-News-66131340/P0FZJ6jm/ZH-HansS](https://www.bbc.com/ws/av-embeds/cps/zhongwen/simp/chinese-news-66131340/p0fzj6jm/zh-hans)![](Images/BBC Chinese/2023-07-07T08-18-28.000Z/p0fzj7g6.jpg)** Your equipment does not support playing multimedia materials ** video plus injection text,

The hot Zibo barbecue and vacant Qingdao real estate reflect the reality of China's economic downturn

In order to understand this in person, we drove from Zibo to east for a few hours and came to a much larger city of Qingdao.

Here, the rapid outbreak of real estate does not match the real needs of buyers or tenants, and as a result, a large number of real estate built is rarely living inside.

A woman sells cold noodles on a mobile booth outside her residential area, and she has very few neighbors.

A few years ago, her husband bought a apartment here after moving to Qingdao. Because I heard that the school here is good, I want to give the child a better starting point.

I asked her if she was worried about her house depreciation.

"Of course worry," she said, "But what can I do?"

A couple next to the street cleaners were stopped for lunch. They pointed at the building behind them and said that no one lived there.

Opposite the road is a small piece of concrete real estate. The outer wall has no painting and no windows. The window frame looks dilapidated because of long exposure.

![](Images/BBC Chinese/2023-07-07T08-18-28.000Z/_130310369_1478460f-0eb1-4546-bae0-e269595e621a.jpg)Image source, Joyce LiU/BBC

Image adding text,

The outbreak of real estate in Qingdao exceeds the needs of buyers and tenants.

"The construction project over there suddenly stopped working last year," the man said.

According to his wife, the entire block is quite deserted. "There is nothing here, there is no gas station, and you have to go far away. Living here is very inconvenient," she said.

This place used to have hope to take off. At that time, the city hosted the Shanghai Cooperation Organization Summit. Chinese President Xi Jinping also recognized the investment and business of this place. Here it may also become the place of the International Expo and other activities.

Originally, there would be people who hired houses, startups, or other companies to buy houses here, but the fact is that there are not many companies.

According to a local real estate agent, the property sales in the area have been halved in recent years.

"The price decline is because of the market saturation," she said. "Too many houses have been built, it is difficult to sell."

We put a drone, and the scene overlooking from the air was worse than we saw on the ground.

A new real estate that is completely stopped around can be seen around, and the real estate that has been completed is almost not angry.

![](Images/BBC Chinese/2023-07-07T08-18-28.000Z/_130310876_infrastructureconstructionsite.jpg)Image source, Joyce LiU/BBC

Image adding text,

The prosperity of China's real estate has made the housing prices in many large cities exceed the ability of ordinary families.

Moreover, supply and demand issues are not unique to this area, or even the city. In China, it is easy to find evidence that real estate bubbles bring in danger.

In this country, one of the reasons for the proliferation of real estate speculation is the lack of other investment options. However, the prosperity of real estate has made the housing prices of many large cities exceed the ability of ordinary families. The government's response to this is to limit the number of personal purchase of houses.

This is a sincere attempt to make equal reforms, but now there is pressure to reverse this direction. In Qingdao, such measures have been relaxed, so as to bring stimulus to the stagnant real estate market.

The challenges faced by Chinese policy makers are to find a way to get economic growth and business confidence from getting rid of the heavy dependence of this real estate sales.He told the BBC in Australia: "China's economy urgently needs to be re -balanced. In the past two or three decades, the Chinese economy has increased huge growth through large -scale infrastructure construction and a substantial growth in the real estate market. The method is not sustainable. "

"Look at the world, developed economies need family as a key driving force for economic growth, and this is not available in China."

From reducing interest rates to cash allowances, the Chinese government is considering promoting individuals and enterprises to increase consumption in various ways.

However, the problem is emotion.

When there are more jobs, people will feel more secure. Enterprises need investment to create more employment opportunities, but when consumers lack security, companies are unwilling to do so.

As Harry Mufi Cruise said: "This is a bit like a chicken and egg. Without corporate expenditure, there will be no economic recovery. They will not spend before they see the recovery. So they become a The deadlock hinders the development of the key part of the economy. "

All these issues may affect global trade.

![](Images/BBC Chinese/2023-07-07T08-18-28.000Z/_130310877_beachtourism1.jpg)Image source, Joyce LiU/BBC

Image adding text,

On the other hand, Qingdao's beach shows that tourism is recovering

China is a big country. The ripples that occur in the world's second largest economy will cause waves.

The production output here has decreased -due to weak international demand -leading to decline in exports and decreased supply in Chinese manufacturing goods globally, the commercial activities of large Asian factories will decrease. After that, China's slowdown consumption means that the import of products of other countries will decrease.

For the Chinese government, the headache may have to make a choice or seek short -term stimulus measures. This will delay the re -balance it needs to face, or to bear more instant pain, so as to start a long -term solution to solve the long -term solution faster plan.

Naturally, there must be almost someone in Beijing's high levels of power. Some people are considering taking some intermediate routes. They first take slightly promoting measures to stabilize the economy, and then consider greater problems on hand.

Because they know that once negative emotions are formed, it may be difficult to reverse the situation.

However, if you want to be optimistic about Qingdao and life itself, you can go to the beach. In the famous coastline here, the tourism industry seems to have recovered.

There is a smile there, a sand castle piled up by tourists. Whether it is an industrial giant or a truck driver, everyone here is enjoying the embrace of the sea.

Whether or not this is in line with reality, here you can hardly feel that although everything is difficult, it will be better in the future.

