![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-07T14-50-24-04-00/000004.png)Articles appearing on the "Netease" on June 22 regarded Biden's "TV speech" as emergency news. The picture intercepts from NetEase [![](Images/rfamandarin/2023-07-07T14-50-24-04-00/000005.png)](https://www.rfa.org/mandarin/shishi-hecha/hc-07072023144404.html/56fe2-622a5716-2023-06-29-14-19-48.png)In the post of posts, some issues said that news sources were reported by Reuters on the 20th.(https://www.reuters.com/world/biden-says-threat-putin-using-tactical-nuclear-weapons-is-real-2023-06-20/)The article quoted Biden's two speeches: The first paragraph was "about two years ago, when I said here that I was worried that the Colorado River was dry, everyone looked at me, just like I was crazy." The second paragraph is "they look at me, just like I said I was worried about Putin's use of tactical nuclear weapons, this is true."

In order to understand the context of Biden's speech, the Asian facts checking the laboratory found a complete press release. This speech took place at a campaign at the Artoreton California on June 19. Biden was mainly talking about climate change at the time.

